defs.name: as_mut_slices

Returns a pair of slices, where the first slice contains the contents

defs.name: tail_head_slice

Returns the slice of uninitialized memory between the `tail` and the

defs.name: try_reserve
defs.value: fn (&mut self, additional: usize) -> Result<(), AllocError>
defs.docs:
Attempts to reserve capacity for inserting at least `additional`
 elements without reallocating. Does nothing if the capacity is already
 sufficient.

defs.name: reserve
defs.docs:
Reserves capacity for inserting at least `additional` elements without
 reallocating. Does nothing if the capacity is already sufficient.

defs.name: reserve_exact
defs.docs:
Reserves the minimum capacity for exactly `additional` more elements to
 be inserted in the given `SliceDeq<T>`. After calling `reserve_exact`,
 capacity will be greater than or equal to `self.len() + additional`.
 Does nothing if the capacity is already sufficient.

defs.name: steal_from_slice
defs.docs:
Steal the elements from the slice `s`. You should `mem::forget` the
 slice afterwards.

defs.name: append
defs.docs: Moves all the elements of `other` into `Self`, leaving `other` empty.

defs.name: front
defs.docs:
Provides a reference to the first element, or `None` if the deque is

defs.name: front_mut

Provides a mutable reference to the first element, or `None` if the
 deque is empty.

defs.name: back
defs.docs:
Provides a reference to the last element, or `None` if the deque is
 empty.

defs.name: back_mut
defs.docs:
Provides a mutable reference to the last element, or `None` if the
 deque is empty.

defs.name: try_push_back
defs.value: fn (&mut self, value: T) -> Result<(), (T, AllocError)>
defs.docs: Attempts to appends `value` to the deque.

defs.name: push_back
defs.docs: Appends `value` to the deque.

defs.name: pop_front
defs.docs:
Removes the first element and returns it, or `None` if the deque is
 empty.

defs.name: pop_back
defs.docs:
Removes the last element from the deque and returns it, or `None` if it
 is empty.

defs.name: shrink_to_fit
defs.docs: Shrinks the capacity of the deque as much as possible.

defs.name: truncate_back
defs.docs: Shortens the deque by removing excess elements from the back.

defs.name: truncate
defs.docs: Shortens the deque by removing excess elements from the back.

defs.name: truncate_front
defs.docs: Shortens the deque by removing excess elements from the front.

defs.name: drain
defs.docs:
Creates a draining iterator that removes the specified range in the
 deque and yields the removed items.

defs.name: clear
defs.docs: Removes all values from the deque.

defs.name: swap_remove_back
defs.docs:
Removes the element at `index` and return it in `O(1)` by swapping the
 last element into its place.

defs.name: swap_remove_front
defs.docs:
Removes the element at `index` and returns it in `O(1)` by swapping the
 first element into its place.

defs.name: insert
defs.value: fn (&mut self, index: usize, element: T) -> ()
defs.docs:
Inserts an `element` at `index` within the deque, shifting all elements
 with indices greater than or equal to `index` towards the back.

defs.name: remove
defs.docs: Removes and returns the element at position `index` within the deque.

defs.name: split_off
defs.docs: Splits the collection into two at the given index.

defs.name: retain
defs.docs: Retains only the elements specified by the predicate.

defs.name: dedup_by_key
defs.value: fn <F, K> (&mut self, mut key: F) -> ()
defs.docs:
Removes all but the first of consecutive elements in the deque that
 resolve to the same key.

defs.name: dedup_by
defs.docs:
Removes all but the first of consecutive elements in the deque
 satisfying a given equality relation.

defs.name: splice
defs.value: fn <R, I> (&mut self, range: R, replace_with: I) -> Splice<I::IntoIter>
defs.docs:
Creates a splicing iterator that replaces the specified range in the
 deque with the given `replace_with` iterator and yields the
 removed items. `replace_with` does not need to be the same length
 as `range`.

defs.name: drain_filter
defs.value: fn <F> (&mut self, filter: F) -> DrainFilter<T, F>
defs.docs:
Creates an iterator which uses a closure to determine if an element
 should be removed.

defs.name: extend_from_slice
defs.docs: Clones and appends all elements in a slice to the `SliceDeque`.

defs.name: resize
defs.value: fn (&mut self, new_len: usize, value: T) -> ()
defs.docs:
Modifies the `SliceDeque` in-place so that `len()` is equal to
 `new_len`, either by removing excess elements or by appending clones of
 `value` to the back.

defs.name: resize_default
defs.docs: Resizes the `SliceDeque` in-place so that `len` is equal to `new_len`.

defs.name: dedup
defs.docs: Removes consecutive repeated elements in the deque.

defs.name: remove_item
